==Grammar==
The Matsés language is primarily suffixing and highly [[Polysynthetic language|synthetic]] with many morphological possibilities and potentially very long words. There is [[body-part prefix]]ation, but no productive [[noun incorporation]] (Fleck 2006b). [[Inflection]]al and class-changing
morphology is fusional, while non-class-changing derivational morphology is mostly [[Agglutinative language|agglutinative]]. Matsés is predominantly “[[dependent-marking language|dependent-marking]]” and uses [[Ergative–absolutive language|ergative–absolutive]] case-marking. Its basic [[word order]] is [[subject–object–verb|SOV]].

==Pisabo "language"==
