{{other people||W. J. Gruffydd (disambiguation){{!}}W. J. Gruffydd}} {{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}}
'''William John Gruffydd''' (1916 – 21 April 2011),<ref>[http://www.anhourago.co.uk/show.aspx?l=8402546&d=501 "Poet WJ Gruffydd dies, aged 94"]</ref> better known by his [[bardic name]] of '''Elerydd''', was a [[Wales|Welsh]] Baptist minister and poet who served as [[Archdruid]] of the [[National Eisteddfod of Wales]] between 1984 and 1987.<ref>[http://www.museumwales.ac.uk/en/894/?display_mode=text National Museum of Wales]</ref>
Like all Archdruids, Elerydd was himself the winner of a major prize at the National Eisteddfod, in his case the crown at the [[Pwllheli]] Eisteddfod in 1955 and at [[Cardiff]] in 1960.
